	<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
	<Accordion>
		<AccordionItem title="How long do Starkey hearing aids last?">
			<p>
				Typically, Starkey hearing aids last between 3–5 years, depending on
				care and daily use. With routine check-ins, many patients experience
				even longer life from their devices.
			</p>
		</AccordionItem>
		<AccordionItem title="Do Starkey hearing aids include tinnitus relief?">
			<p>
				Yes. Many Starkey hearing aids include built-in tinnitus support
				features designed to help reduce the perception of ringing, buzzing, or
				other phantom sounds. These tools can be customized by your audiologist
				to match your specific tinnitus experience and level of discomfort.
			</p>
			<p>
				Starkey devices often use soothing sound therapy options, such as white
				noise or nature sounds, which can help mask tinnitus and make it less
				noticeable throughout the day. Because the settings are highly
				adjustable, your audiologist can fine-tune the therapy to provide the
				right level of relief while still maintaining clear, natural hearing in
				everyday environments.
			</p>
		</AccordionItem>
		<AccordionItem title="Can I stream calls and music with Starkey devices?">
			<p>
				Yes. Most modern Starkey hearing aids support direct Bluetooth®
				streaming and app-based control through My Starkey or Thrive.
			</p>
		</AccordionItem>
	</Accordion>

